      • GenerateCTiles

        private java.util.List<TableauNode> GenerateCTiles(AndNode andNode)
        Generate the CTiles by expanding the AX, EX as explained in Emerson and Clarke 82.

        AX can be satisfied easily by not having any children, however, EX forces at least one child, thus, that child must satisfy AX.

        AX and EX can have process indices, in which case children resulting from an EX_i must satisfy the AX_i conditions and the other AXs don't matter.

        Parameters:
        andNode - the AndNode to generate CTiles for.
        Returns:
        a list of OrNodes that are the CTiles.
